            Slug = "invoices-reference",
            Summary = "Power-user and admin reference for invoices: multi-currency/FX, the invoice queue mode, email/PDF endpoints, draft auto-save, and role + capability gating.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Reference,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 90,
            AppRoutes = """["/invoices"]""",
            Tags = """["invoices","reference","advanced"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Multi-currency & FX\n\nThe invoice header carries an optional `CurrencyId` and `FxRate` (passed through `CreateInvoiceRequestModel` to `CreateInvoiceCommand`). Both are **additive and hidden on single-currency installs**:\n\n- The **currency selector** only renders when more than one *active* currency exists (`ActiveCurrencyService.listActiveCurrencies()` returns >1). One-currency shops never see it.\n- The form defaults `currencyId` to the **base currency** (`isBaseCurrency`, falling back to the first active currency) and `fxRate` to `1`.\n- The **FX-rate input** only renders when a *non-base* currency is selected. For the base currency the rate is implicitly 1 and the field stays hidden. `fxRate` validates as required, `min` 0.0000001.\n- Line amounts are entered in the chosen currency; FX is the conversion back to the base book currency. Single-currency installs are unaffected — the whole block is inert.\n\n## Invoice queue settings\n\nTwo `SystemSetting` rows drive how new invoices are routed, read via `GET /api/v1/invoices/queue-settings` and written via `PUT /api/v1/invoices/queue-settings`:\n\n- `invoice_mode` — `\"direct\"` (default) or `\"managed\"`. Direct = anyone permitted creates invoices inline; managed = invoices route to an assignee's queue.\n- `invoice_queue_assignee` — the user id (stored as text) that managed-mode invoices are assigned to. The GET resolves it to `assignedUserName`.\n\n**Read** is allowed for `Admin, Manager, OfficeManager`; **write** (`PUT`) is **Admin-only**. The response model is `InvoiceQueueSettingsResponse(Mode, AssignedUserId, AssignedUserName)`.\n\n## Email & PDF (endpoints exist; not yet surfaced)\n\nThe controller already exposes these, but the list/detail UI does not yet wire buttons to them — they are API-ready:\n\n- `GET /api/v1/invoices/{id}/pdf` — server-rendered PDF via QuestPDF (`GenerateInvoicePdfQuery`), returned as `invoice-{id}.pdf`.\n- `POST /api/v1/invoices/{id}/email` — body `{ recipientEmail }` (`SendInvoiceEmailCommand`). Dispatch goes through `IIntegrationOutboxService` with an idempotency key `invoice-email:{id}:{recipient}`, so re-sends to the same address de-duplicate.\n\nUntil the buttons land, these are reachable only via direct API call.\n\n## Draft auto-save & resume\n\nThe create dialog is a `DraftableForm` registered with `entityType: 'invoice'` (see the Form Draft system). Dirty form state auto-saves to IndexedDB and survives logout, refresh, and tab close. On the list page, `InvoicesComponent.ngOnInit()` calls `DraftResumeService.consume('invoice')` — if a pending invoice draft exists, the create dialog **re-opens automatically** so the user can finish where they left off.\n\n## Roles & capability gating\n\n- The whole `InvoicesController` is `[Authorize(Roles = \"Admin,Manager,OfficeManager\")]` and `[RequiresCapability(\"CAP-O2C-INVOICE\")]`. Engineers and shop-floor roles have no invoice access.\n- `CAP-O2C-INVOICE` is **default-on**, area `O2C`. It gates sales-side invoice generation post-ship. The application-resident invoice entity exists in built-in accounting mode; in connected-accounting mode the invoice is exported to QB and is **read-only** locally (the ⚡ accounting boundary — see the Overview module).\n- The AP twin is `CAP-P2P-BILL` (vendor bills); the two are symmetric across the order-to-cash / procure-to-pay split.\n- `DELETE /api/v1/invoices/{id}` carries `[IfMatch(typeof(Invoice))]` — it requires an `If-Match` ETag for optimistic-concurrency safety, and (per the lifecycle rules) only Draft invoices are deletable.","sections":[]}"""
        });

        Log.Information("Seeded Invoices training modules");
    }
}
